```julia
function clean_column(col::String)
    return lowercase(replace(strip(col), r"[-\s]" => "_"))
end
```

This function takes a string `col` representing a column name and returns the cleaned version of the column name. It first lowers the case using the `lowercase()` function, then strips any leading or trailing whitespaces with `strip(col)`, and finally replaces all spaces and hyphens with an underscore using `replace(..., r"[-\s]" => "_")`. The regular expression `r"[-\s]"` matches any hyphen (`-`) or whitespace character.
